The President, Major General Muhammadu Buhari (retd.), will on Friday (tomorrow) address the nation in commemoration of this year’s Democracy Day. According to a statement on Thursday by his Special Adviser on Media and Publicity, Femi Adesina, the President’s message will be broadcast by 7am. The statement read, “To commemorate Nigeria’s Democracy Day, President Muhammadu Buhari will broadcast to the nation on Friday, June 12, 2020, at 7am. “Television and radio stations as well as other electronic media outlets are enjoined to hook up to the network services of the Nigerian Television Authority and Radio Nigeria respectively for the broadcast.”  President Muhammadu Buhari will hold a national address today (Monday) by 7pm. This was contained in a statement by Special Adviser to the President on Media and Publicity, Femi Adesina. The statement read, “President Muhammadu Buhari will broadcast to the nation Monday, April 13, 2020 at 7pm. “Television, radio and… April 13, 2020 In "News" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - As the number of cases of Covid-19 continues to increase, President Buhari is set to address the country, Monday April 13 7 pm. A statement signed by his Senior Special Assistant Media Femi Adesina directs all media houses to hook up live to… April 13, 2020 In "Top Stories" President Muhammadu Buhari will address the nation on Monday by8:00pm. A statement by his Special Adviser on Media and Publicity, Femi Adesina, disclosed this. “President Muhammadu Buhari will address the nation Monday, April 27, 2020 at 8pm. “Television, radio and other electronic media stations are enjoined to hook up to… April 27, 2020 In "News"